element UFXMsg
diagram
type W4M_Msg
properties
content complex
attributes
Name  Type  Use  Default  Fixed  Annotation
scheme  W4D_Code  optional      
appinfo
Scheme name. The name specifies the scheme that will be used for xml validation. Supported values: WAY4Appl,  WAY4Appl, WAY4UDoc, WAY4USec, WAY4Profile. Value depends on msg_type attribute. The correspondence between attributes as follows:
scheme="WAY4Appl" for msg_type="Application" ,
scheme="WAY4Appl" for msg_type="Information",
scheme="WAY4UDoc" for msg_type="Doc",
scheme="WAY4USec" for msg_type="Security",
scheme="WAY4Profile" for msg_type="CustomerProfile"
scheme="WAY4Appl" for msg_type="TariffData"
scheme="WAY4OfficerAppl" for msg_type="OfficerApplication"
msg_type  W4D_Code  required      
appinfo
Message Type. It defines the type of an application layer message. The value also defines the element which is presented in the UFXMsg/MsgData aggregate. Supported values:
Application, Information, Doc, Security, CustomerProfile, etc.
direction  W4D_RqRs  optional      
appinfo
Message direction. Supported values: Rq - request; Rs - response;  Notif - notification.
version  W4D_Code  required      
appinfo
Format version. Current version is 2.3.12. Supported values 2.0, 2.1, 2.2, 2.3, 2.3.02, 2.3.04, 2.3.06, 2.3.08, 2.3.10, 2.3.12.
session  W4D_Code  optional      
appinfo
Session identifier
resp_class  derived by: xs:string  optional      
appinfo
Message severity code. Supported values: 'F' -  Fatal Error, 'E' -  Error, 'I' - Information, or 'W' - Warning
resp_code  W4D_Counter  optional      
appinfo
Response code. See following sections of UFX specification for details: "Chapter 5. Response Processing Guidelines", "Appendix 1. WAY4 UFX Response Codes".
resp_text  W4D_String  optional      
appinfo
Response message. See following sections of UFX specification for details: "Chapter 5. Response Processing Guidelines", "Appendix 1. WAY4 UFX Response Codes".

element W4M_Msg/MsgId
diagram
type W4D_MsgId
properties
content simple
facets
Kind Value Annotation
minLength 1
maxLength 36
annotation
appinfo
Message identifier. This identifier may be used by message sender for extended matching response messages with requests. It is recommended to generate value for this element basing on an "Universally Unique IDentifier (UUID) URN Namespace", RFC 4122 specification. This RFC may be downloaded from http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4122.txt.

Following fields are supported in local language (Language != "ENG"): Country, AddressZip, City, AddressLocation, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, AddressLine4, and MunicipalityCode. Following fields are supported in English (Language = "ENG"): City, AddressLine1, AddressLine2, AddressLine3, and AddressLine4

Actions applied to the object: "Add" - add object, "AddOrUpdate" - add or update object, "Update" - update object, "ActivatePersonal" - activate personal object parameters, "ActivateIndividual" - activate personal parameters of an object created on the basis of a template that is later detached, "ActivateStandard" - activate standard object parameters, "Disable" - disable object parameters, "Delete" - delete object. complexType W4DC_TransTypeParms
diagram

element W4DC_TransTypeParms/TransCode
diagram
type W4DC_TransCode
properties
content complex
annotation
appinfo
TransCode - Transaction type determiner. There are some dictionaries allowing Transition Types to be defined. Therefore, there are some cases of Type definition. Supported dictionaries:  1. Message Type. A message type code is placed in the MsgCode element. 2. Order. An order's Payment Type code is placed in ServiceCode; Order Code is placed in ServiceCodeExt. MsgCode is filled with "OrdReq" for requests, "OrdRev" for reverse messages, or "OrdAdv" for advice messages. 3. Additional Service Type. An Additional Service Type code is placed in the ServiceCode element. MsgCode is filled with AddServReq for requests.
